BUON APPETITO 
Leaning toward Italian? 
Market City Caffe, 33 S. Fair Oaks, Pasadena. (818) 568-0203. Style: Storefront 
look, ample antipasto bar. Setting: Bricks and beams. Recommended: Pizza 
portofino; grilled veal chop; tirami su. Cost per person: $10-$25. 
Osteria Nonni, 3219 Glendale Blvd., Atwater. (213) 666-7133. Style: Trendy 
Angeli clone. Setting: Pseudo-industrial. Recommended: Pizza ai quattro 
stagioni; croquettes di patate; spaghetti puttanesca. Cost: $10-$20. 
Pazzia, 755 N. La Cienega, Los Angeles. (213) 657-9271. Style: A fine madness 
by the man who opened Rex. Setting: Designer-gorgeous: Ricci silverware, Aldo 
Rossi chairs. Recommended: Pappa al pomodoro; yellow pepper soup; ravioli with 
lentils and pine nuts. Cost per person: $25-$40. 
Trovare, 21618 Ventura Blvd., Woodland Hills. (818) 340-4451. Style: Where the 
West Valley chic eat Italian. Setting: Mirrors, furs, acrylic nails. 
Recommended: Calamari fritti; Scottish salmon; Trovare scampi. Cost per person: 
$12-$30. 
Zio and Company, 5242 Van Nuys Blvd., Sherman Oaks. (818) 784-8051. Style: Part 
imported food market, part neighborhood restaurant -- all home-style cooking. 
Setting: Larger-than-life papier-mache figurative sculptures. Recommended: 
Lasagne; linguine with black mussels; lemon roasted chicken. Cost per person: 
$15-25. Kathie Jenkins 
